<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 7:28PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL CENTRE COUNTY
THROUGH 800 PM EDT...
At 728 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bellefonte, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lamar, Zion, Millheim, Aaronsburg, Rebersburg, Spring Mills, Coburn
and Madisonburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
